quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  9,118,"As for the three who we behind, until the earth seemed too cramped for them, spacious though and even their souls seemed to strangle them and they thought there be no refuge from Allah (God) except through Himself-, then He turned [in Mercy] towards them so they might repent. Allah (God) is Ever-Turning, Merciful."
  9,119,"You who believe, heed Allah (God) and stand by those who are truthful."
  9,120,"It is not for the people of Madina nor any desert Arabs who (live) around them, to lag behind Allah (God)'s messenger [in marching] nor to prefer themselves ahead of himself. That is so no thirst would afflict them, nor any stress nor starvation along Allah (God)'s way, nor would they adopt any stand which irritate disbelievers, nor gain any acquisition from an enemy, unless some good deeds were recorded for them because of it. Allah (God) does not waste the wages of those who do good,"
  9,121,"They could not provide for any outlay small or great, nor cut across a valley unless it were prescribed for them, so that Allah (God) may reward them for the finest things they have been doing."
  9,122,"Believers should not march forth in a body; if a squadron from each division of them should march forth, they should still instruct [others] in religion and warn their folk when they return to them so that they may take precautions."